22
23 WHEREAS, John W. Walker, Sr. was born on June 3, 1937, in Hope,
24 Arkansas, and died October 28, 2019, at the age of eighty-two (82); and
25
26 WHEREAS, John W. Walker, Sr. was an attorney, a civil rights activist,
27 and a politician who served as a member of the House of Representatives from
28 January 2011 until his death in 2019; and
29
30 WHEREAS, John W. Walker, Sr. attended Henry C. Yerger High School in
31 Hope, one of the few schools in rural Arkansas that provided a high school
32 curriculum to Black children, before moving with his family to Houston,
33 Texas, in 1952 and graduating from all-Black Jack Yates High School in 1954;
34 and
35
36 WHEREAS, John W. Walker, Sr. was the first Black undergraduate student
